The '''Beehive Boot''', which signifies instate [[American football|football]] supremacy among [[Division I]] universities from the state of [[Utah]], was conceived in [[1971]]. The authentic [[pioneer]] boot, which is estimated to be well over 100 years old, is awarded annually to the Utah school with the best record against its instate NCAA Division I foes. The schools who compete for the boot are [[Utah Utes football|Utah]], [[BYU Cougars football|Brigham Young]], [[Utah State Aggies|Utah State]], and [[Weber State]]. However, because Weber State plays in the [[Championship Subdivision]] of Division I, they rarely play any of their interstate foes, and thus have never won the boot. In fact, the Wildcats are just 1-15 against BYU, Utah, and Utah State in the 36 years that the trophy has existed, their lone win being a 44-25 victory over Utah State in 1978.
